My FRIEND @brianbenjaminny was WRONGED by the federal government and the state of NY. He had and still has a very promising career as a progressive voice in the state. He became Lt. Governor because Andrew Cuomo had to resign…

He was chosen because he’s SOLID, intelligent, hard working, reasonable, fair, TRUST WORTHY and a fighter for justice. A white man who was under indictment for some other criminal charges tried to implicate Brian in what was clearly an attempt to pass the buck. 
It was a witch hunt for something Brian would NEVER DO. Never. 

He was about to win a race to be seated as an elected Lt. Governor, rather than just appointed by the Governor. THESE BULLSHIT CHARGES that the feds of the NY Southern District helped “trump” up on him caused him to suspend his campaign and resign from office. 

This man has a beautiful wife, my sister @catmbenjamin, and two beautiful daughters. His family had been humiliated and disrespected. His mother’s heart was broke in pieces. The money they spent on expensive lawyers. 

Now the case is dismissed and whattttt?????? 

Lord help my blood pressure today! I agree with every word @tamikadmallory!!!!

Nothing more left to say! Go vote tomorrow Georgia residents. We have too much to lose! Keep @raphaelwarnock in office! We can’t have a Trump appointed representative in office. It will be a losing battle getting bills past, protecting the most marginalized and the fight for equality will be harder. Let’s VOTE!!

@yelleskincare was created at a time I was at my worse. As people there will come a time you need to lean on your support system. I thought of this imagery for multiple reasons but the main person one was I was falling. Deep in to depression, deep into a lonely place, deep into hiding what I was feeling and going through. I was a new mom, my husband had to leave me and the industry turned its back on me. My friends…my small village met me where I was. They held, they let me lean on them and they never judged me. Our skin processes stress in all kinds of ways. Dark spots, acne break outs, dry patches, dull loose skin. All of which can make you feel even worse. I’ve never talked publicly much about this time because many of you saw it in TV. But now I’m ready.

Engaging in a holistic self-care routine such as YELLE Skincare, has been clinically proven to reduce or eliminate anxiety and depression, reduce stress, increase happiness, and more. It can help you adapt to changes, build strong relationships, and recover from setbacks.

Transparency moment…@mendeecees and I celebrated an anniversary last week. We were beefing. Just not seeing eye to eye, went to our sons graduation, I had a booking, left town came back on our anniversary, went to our friends pajama party and barely spoke. We’ve talked, disagreed, talked some more, silent treatment some more, then talked again. If you notice we didn’t post eachother, nor did we even say Happy Anniversary to eachother. Did y’all notice I didn’t post him in any of the graduation pictures??? Lol yes I’m petty. Here’s the point of all this, we’re not perfect, we go through it all the time, but not once did I or we decide to leave each other. We smiled for pictures together at the pajama party, went home together, supported our children together and still supported each other while not liking each other very much. We had talk more. Mad but listening and hearing in love what was being expressed and felt. Marriage won’t always be sun shining days, some days it’s gloomy and it feels like it’s pouring raining in your home. June 1st is here and for me it represents a new start, a fresh start. @mendeecees I’m thankful for you. This is my sister @lsarsour. We’ve fought together, slept in jail cells together, cried many times over the injustice happening to blacks/minorities, indigenous/members of the LGBTQIA+ communities, together. Now she is hurting, we are hurting with her. She is one of the most kindest, gentlest warrior flowers I know. I can’t sit back an act like I’m not enraged with her. Over the past few days I’ve seen so many innocent children and women be the victims of war crimes and hatred, I can’t take it! And I’m not even there. Imagine living in these countries. Where is the humanity in us? How do we move as one world, with genocide and apartheid running rampant in our neighboring nations?  Here is something Linda said that we must take heed to  @lsarsour “Anyone cheering on the US backed Israeli apartheid regime’s response to collectively punish and massacre Palestinians doesn’t give a damn about safety of Jews in Israel. Violence begets violence. The cycle will continue & the vengeance will only grow deeper. This is the moment for all of us to stand together and demand loud and clear the END OF THE OCCUPATION & LIFTING OF THE SIEGE ON GAZA. 

Palestinians are not the enemies of the Jews. The enemy here is apartheid. Apartheid divides and lies to people. Apartheid leads you to believe that the only way you can achieve safety and security is at the expense of another people. Apartheid convinces you that there’s nothing wrong with dehumanizing, caging, depriving, killing, detaining Palestinians if that means you get to live a “normal” life. Apartheid LIED. 

Safety of one is predicated on the safety of all. No one can be safe if everyone is not safe. No one is truly free unless we are all free. That’s why Free Palestine is a call for freedom and Justice for Palestinians and the safety of ALL people. 

Last night, I was awoken by my nightmares of explosions and children screaming, begging to live, begging to be safe from bombs. Think of the children. Think of the future we want them to live in. “

@lsarsour I love you so much. I know you and how you hurt for the people. All people. Sister I am with you in spirit and in mind. I love you.

We get asked a lot, what are peptides? And how can one of our custom serums give you a boost? 

Peptides are small chains of amino acids that act as messengers in your skin, sending signals to stimulate collagen production, enhance elasticity, and promote a more youthful complexion.

When applied topically, YELLE Skincare’s peptide boosting serum can:

1. Boost Collagen Production: Peptides signal your skin to produce more collagen, which helps to diminish the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles, and sagging skin. This can result in firmer, plumper, and more youthful-looking skin over time.

2. Improve Skin Elasticity: Peptides help to improve the elasticity of your skin, making it more resilient and able to bounce back from daily stressors. This can lead to a smoother, tighter, and more lifted appearance.

3. Enhance Skin Texture: Peptides work to refine the skin’s texture, promoting a smoother and more even complexion. They can help minimize the appearance of pores, acne scars, and other surface imperfections.

4. Aid in Skin Repair: Peptides have been shown to support the skin’s natural healing process by assisting in repairing damaged tissues. This can be beneficial for reducing the appearance of sun damage, hyperpigmentation, and other signs of aging.

Overall, our peptide boosting serum is an excellent addition to your skincare routine, helping to nourish and revitalize your skin from within. So, if you’re looking to achieve a more youthful, firm, and radiant complexion, incorporating a peptide serum can be a game-changer!

We KNOW you’ve heard to only use a pea sized amount of product, but why do we suggest this?

Most people tend to apply more product than necessary. Using excessive amounts of skincare products can often be wasteful and may not provide any additional benefits. 

Additionally, using too much product may overwhelm the skin and lead to potential issues like clogged pores or irritation. 

Then what happens?

Your body goes into overdrive trying to now correct new problems. You buy more and more skincare products with tons of chemicals, only to see issues worsen. Finally, you turn to a trusted esthetician, such as our partner @__sparklenshine to truly educate you on taking care of your skin. 😩It’s a cycle!
